whereas.text:
Whereas there are millions of unparented children in the world, including 402,378 children in the
			 foster care system in the United States, approximately 102,000 of whom are
			 waiting for families to adopt them;

Whereas every day, loving and nurturing families are strengthened and expanded when committed and
			 dedicated individuals make an important difference in the life of a child
			 through adoption;

Whereas while 4 in 10 Americans have considered adoption, a majority of Americans have
			 misperceptions about the process of adopting children from foster care and
			 the children who are eligible for adoption;

Whereas 39 percent of Americans believe that foster care adoption is expensive, when in reality
			 there is no substantial cost for adopting from foster care and financial
			 support is available to adoptive parents after the adoption is finalized;

Whereas family reunification, kinship care, and domestic and inter-county adoption promote
			 permanency and stability to a far greater degree than long-term
			 institutionalization and long-term, often disrupted foster care;

Whereas in 2013, nearly 400 events were held in the United States,
			 finalizing the adoptions of approximately 4,500 children from foster care;
			 and
